# Daily job digest for 2026-03-20

Summary:
- Found 3 additional new roles on this pass from the allowed source set.
- Today's digest now contains 8 roles worth noting: 5 strong matches and 3 borderline / maybe matches.

## Strong matches

### 1. Cryptography Researcher — ClairVault
- Fit score: 9/10
- Location: Remote or hybrid
- Link: https://www.iacr.org/jobs/item/4060
- Direct fit to the profile: the posting explicitly asks for homomorphic encryption, lattice cryptography, MPC, and zero-knowledge proofs.
- The role is research-engineering shaped rather than purely academic: design protocols, analyze security and efficiency, and work with Rust developers on production libraries.
- Startup setting and privacy-preserving data systems align well with the profile's applied-crypto and real-world-impact preferences.

### 2. Applied Cryptographer — Hashgraph
- Fit score: 8.5/10
- Location: Remote
- Link: https://www.hashgraph.com/careers/?gh_jid=8284328002
- Explicit applied-cryptography role: the posting names ZKPs, MPC, homomorphic encryption, TEEs, and privacy-by-design features.
- Strong research-to-product fit: design and optimize cryptographic primitives and protocols, benchmark them, and work closely with engineers and product.
- Main concern: the work is tightly tied to Hedera and secure smart-contract / blockchain infrastructure.

### 3. Cryptography Engineer — QEDIT
- Fit score: 8.5/10
- Location: unknown
- Link: https://qed-it.com/careers
- The role is explicitly for a hands-on cryptography engineer or cryptography researcher and centers on zero-knowledge proofs, elliptic-curve cryptography, and Rust.
- Core work is a strong match for the research-plus-engineering profile: design protocols, implement them, and review cryptographic code.
- Main concern: the role is blockchain-heavy and the public page does not state location or remote policy.

### 4. Software Developer (m/w/d) Schwerpunkt Kryptographie — secunet Security Networks AG
- Fit score: 8/10
- Location: Berlin or Eschborn
- Link: https://jobs.secunet.com/Software-Developer-mwd-Schwerpunkt-Kryptographie-de-j3332.html
- Strong topical match: post-quantum migration, ECC/PQC cryptography, PKI, Common Criteria, and smartcard-platform work.
- Berlin is a preferred geography and the posting explicitly allows mobile office plus limited EU remote work.
- Main concern: the stack leans toward C/C++, smartcard platform work, and possibly team leadership, which is narrower than the shared profile.

### 5. (Senior) Software Engineer (m/f/d) - Network Security — secunet Security Networks AG
- Fit score: 7.8/10
- Location: Berlin, Bonn, Dresden, Eschborn, Essen, Hamburg, Hannover, Ilmenau, München or Stuttgart
- Link: https://jobs.secunet.com/Senior-Software-Engineer-mfd-Network-Security-de-j3322.html
- Strong security-engineering fit: trust establishment, mTLS, IPSec, WireGuard, secure networking, and Linux-platform work.
- The stack is technically serious and relevant to the profile: Rust, NixOS, upstream open-source work, PQC, Secure Boot, and TPM2.
- Main concern: this is more OS / platform security engineering than core cryptography research.

## Borderline / maybe

### 6. Software Developer (m/w/d) Smartcard — secunet Security Networks AG
- Fit score: 7/10
- Location: Berlin, Dresden or Eschborn
- Link: https://jobs.secunet.com/Software-Developer-mwd-Smartcard-de-j3333.html
- Relevant because it sits on a smartcard trust anchor and explicitly asks for deep ECC/PQC cryptography knowledge.
- Germany-based locations, technical depth, and security-critical product work fit the general preference set.
- Main concern: Java Card, embedded software, and hardware-adjacent standards are central, and those are not evidenced in the profile.

### 7. Technischer Berater (m/w/d) - EUDI Wallet & Digitale Identitäten — secunet Security Networks AG
- Fit score: 6.9/10
- Location: Germany-wide
- Link: https://jobs.secunet.com/Technischer-Berater-mwd-EUDI-Wallet-Digitale-Identitaeten-de-j3146.html
- Good topical overlap with the track: EUDI Wallet, digital identity, verifiable credentials, OpenID4VC, DIDComm, OAuth2, SAML, and PKI.
- German plus English fluency and the feasible public-sector / technical-specialist pivot make it practically plausible.
- Main concern: the role is advisory and integration-heavy rather than research-engineering heavy.

### 8. Hardware Verification Engineer — PQShield
- Fit score: 6/10
- Location: Remote in UK, Germany, France, Belgium, Austria, Netherlands or Spain
- Link: https://pqshield.com/careers/apply/4682388101/
- The role is clearly security-relevant and asks for background in software development, cryptography, and secure product development.
- Geography is workable from Germany and PQShield is directly on-track as a post-quantum cryptography company.
- Main concern: the job is fundamentally a UVM / formal hardware verification role, so it is a stretch against the shared research-engineering profile.

## Notes

- Zama currently exposes relevant indexed roles, especially `Rust Engineer, Coprocessor`, but the best-matching openings carried East Coast US / Canada eligibility constraints or unstable live pages, so they were excluded conservatively.
- SandboxAQ surfaced `Staff Software Engineer, Cryptography R&D`, but the official Ashby page remained JavaScript-only in this environment, so it was not added without a verifiable official posting body.
- Roseman Labs, Duality Technologies, Partisia Blockchain, Least Authority, Trail of Bits, NEC Laboratories Europe, Infineon, Quantinuum, Qrypt, QuSecure, and Rambus did not surface a verifiable current role that beat the bar above from the allowed source pages.
